# Implementation Plan - BLoC Migration & Immersive UI

This plan outlines the steps to migrate the `RestaurantOrderSystem` from Riverpod to **BLoC (Business Logic Component)** architecture, as requested, to achieve a more advanced and scalable state management system. It also includes "Immersive" UI upgrades.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is a **major architectural refactor**. Existing Riverpod `ConsumerWidget`s will be converted to `StatelessWidget`s/`StatefulWidget`s using `BlocBuilder` and `BlocListener`.
> We will start with **Authentication**, then **Menu**, then **Cart/Order**.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Dependencies
#### [MODIFY] pubspec.yaml
- Add `flutter_bloc` and `equatable`.
- Keep `flutter_riverpod` temporarily to avoid immediate build breaks, but aim to remove it.

### 2. Architecture Setup
#### [NEW] lib/core/di/dependency_injection.dart
- (Optional) Use `get_it` or `RepositoryProvider` to inject Repositories (`AuthRepository`, `ProductRepository`, etc.) so BLoCs can access them without Riverpod.

### 3. Feature: Authentication (Priority #1)
#### [NEW] lib/features/auth/presentation/bloc/auth_event.dart
- `AuthCheckRequested`
- `AuthLoginRequested(email, password)`
- `AuthLogoutRequested`

#### [NEW] lib/features/auth/presentation/bloc/auth_state.dart
- `AuthInitial`, `AuthLoading`, `AuthAuthenticated`, `AuthUnauthenticated`, `AuthFailure`

#### [NEW] lib/features/auth/presentation/bloc/auth_bloc.dart
- Implementation of the BLoC logic.

#### [MODIFY] lib/features/auth/presentation/login_screen.dart
- Convert `ConsumerWidget` to `StatefulWidget`.
- Use `BlocConsumer` to handle loading indicators and navigation.
- **Immersive UI**: Add animated background or entrance animations using `flutter_animate`.

#### [MODIFY] lib/main.dart
- Wrap the app in `MultiRepositoryProvider` and `MultiBlocProvider`.

- Create `MenuBloc` (`LoadMenu`, `FilterCategory`).
